### HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol):
Jab bhi tum kisi website ko open karte ho — jaise Google.com — tumhara browser us website ke server se baat karta hai. Jo tareeqa dono ke darmiyan baat karne ka hota hai usay HTTP kehte hain.
Ye protocol Tim Berners-Lee ne 1989-1991 ke darmiyan banaya tha. Iska kaam sirf yeh hai ke website ki cheezein jaise HTML, images, videos waghera tum tak pohanchayein — lekin yeh secure nahi hota, koi beech mein dekh bhi sakta hai.

---

### HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure):
Ab yeh HTTP ka secure version hai. Iska matlab yeh hai ke jab tum kisi website se data bhej rahe ho ya le rahe ho, toh yeh data encrypt hota hai — yani koi beech mein na dekh sakta hai, na chori kar sakta hai.

Iska dusra fayda yeh hai ke tumhein yeh bhi confirm hota hai ke jis website se baat ho rahi hai, woh asli hai, koi nakli ya fake website nahi.

---

##### Agar tum penetration testing kar rahe ho, toh yaad rakhna:

HTTP websites par sniffing ya MITM attacks asaan hote hain.

HTTPS mein tumhein pehlay encryption todna parta hai, ya phishing ya certificate bypass jaise tricks use karni padti hain.

